# Validation & DTO standards

## DTO rules

- One DTO per use case: `CreateXDto`, `UpdateXDto`, `XQueryDto`.
- Use `class-validator` decorators on all request DTOs.
- Required fields: `@IsNotEmpty()` or type-specific validators (`@IsEmail()`, `@IsUUID()`).
- Optional fields: `@IsOptional()` **before** other validators.
- Enums: `@IsEnum(MyEnum)` with shared domain enum.
- No validation logic in controllers — rely on DTO + global `ValidationPipe`.

## Flag

- Controller methods accepting `any`, untyped body, or `@Body()` without a DTO class.
- Missing validation on write endpoints (POST, PUT, PATCH).
- User-controlled fields written directly to Prisma without allowlisting (mass assignment).
- Query params parsed as strings without `@Type(() => Number)` when numeric.

## Response shapes

- Use response DTOs when the project pattern exists; otherwise typed interfaces are acceptable.
- Do not return raw Prisma entities with sensitive fields (passwords, tokens) if added later.
